1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,169
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:06,131
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:10,677
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,760 --> 00:00:12,846
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:14,973
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:15,056 --> 00:00:16,141
[Raki] That's Enzo.

7
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:17,600
[Atoy] <i>Enzo got Queenie.</i>

8
00:00:17,684 --> 00:00:18,893
Your replacement is already here.

9
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:20,437
- Tonet!
- [gasps]

10
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,646
Where did you hide Tonet?

11
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:22,731
[Enzo] <i>So, you're her brother.</i>

12
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:23,898
<i>Aren't you mad at her?</i>

13
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:25,191
[Emerson] <i>I'm just hurt. That's different.</i>

14
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:27,193
[Atoy] <i>Son of a thread.</i>

15
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:28,987
[grunts, shouts]

16
00:00:29,738 --> 00:00:30,697
[Tonet] <i>Is Big Brother there?</i>

17
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:31,781
PREVIOUSLY

18
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:34,325
<i>That person shouldn't be with Emerson.</i>

19
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:36,286
- [gunshot]
- [gasps]

20
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:37,912
[shrieks, gasping]

21
00:00:37,996 --> 00:00:38,913
[Atoy] <i>Just a moment, I'll be back.</i>

22
00:00:38,997 --> 00:00:40,331
<i>I'll be back. Stay right there.</i>

23
00:00:40,415 --> 00:00:43,168
- [grunting and groaning]
- [thumping]

24
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:45,211
[intense music playing]

25
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:47,255
[Tonet shouting] <i>Atoy!</i>

26
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:49,424
[sobbing] Atoy… Atoy!

27
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:52,135
[Tess] <i>Why don't you have a scar?</i>

28
00:00:52,218 --> 00:00:55,013
[Tess] Isn't the wound supposed
to be around here?

29
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:56,264
So, you're a doctor, huh?

30
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:57,557
Sorry, ma'am.

31
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:00,977
Audrey Regalia has sent me
several messages.

32
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:04,272
[Mercado] <i>Asking about</i>
<i>your meet-up schedule.</i>

33
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:06,399
[Atoy] <i>I'm just finishing up a job, sir.</i>

34
00:01:06,483 --> 00:01:09,069
- [Mercado, in English] <i>How was it?</i>
- Let's just say that…

35
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:11,446
[Atoy] <i>There's no tear</i>
<i>that cannot be sewn.</i>

36
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:13,114
Do you know where she's going?

37
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:16,117
[Red] <i>To the… Master Cutter, I think.</i>

38
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,660
<i>That's what I heard.</i>

39
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:19,537
[Dmitri, in English] <i>No. No way.</i>

40
00:01:19,621 --> 00:01:21,873
<i>That Master Cutter is not a tailor.</i>

41
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:30,381
[music swells]

42
00:01:30,465 --> 00:01:32,634
[music fades]

43
00:01:32,717 --> 00:01:36,596
[suspicious music playing]

44
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,808
Thank you.

45
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:42,852
- Yes, ma'am?
- Um, where is the garden area here?

46
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:44,187
It's by the stairs.

47
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:46,523
When you go up to the second floor,
you'll see it there.

48
00:01:46,606 --> 00:01:48,149
- Ah, okay. Thank you, thank you.
- Okay.

49
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:50,652
[music continues]

50
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:51,861
- Uh, miss.
- [in English] Yes, sir?

51
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:54,489
Please check Dr. Villarama's schedule.

52
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:57,325
- I went to her clinic, but it was closed.
- When is this, sir? Please fill this out.

53
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:59,786
- [in English] Can I have a pen?
- I'm in a hurry.

54
00:01:59,869 --> 00:02:02,372
[in English] Miss, miss! Your shades!

55
00:02:02,455 --> 00:02:04,124
Wait. Miss!

56
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:06,334
- Ah, miss.
- Miss… Sir?

57
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:08,294
- [receptionist] Miss?
- Do you want me to give it to her?

58
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:09,254
[receptionist] Is that okay, sir?

59
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:10,088
- [Atoy] Yes.
- In the garden.

60
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:12,090
- I'll just hand it to her.
- [receptionist] Okay. Thank you.

61
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:13,424
Uh, what…

62
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:15,218
She's wearing a yellow blouse.

63
00:02:15,301 --> 00:02:16,636
And she has long hair, sir.

64
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:17,762
- [in English] Yellow.
- [receptionist] Thank you, sir.

65
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:20,140
- Sorry. What can I do for you?
- Okay.

66
00:02:20,932 --> 00:02:23,226
- Ah, it's okay now, miss.
- Here, please.

67
00:02:23,309 --> 00:02:24,310
- Are you ready?
- She already texted.

68
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:25,353
- Yes, she already texted.
- Okay.

69
00:02:25,436 --> 00:02:28,106
[suave theme music playing]

70
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,524
[motorcycle revving]

71
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,905
[machine whirring]

72
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:37,323
[sewing machine whirring]

73
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:38,700
[gun cocks]

74
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,160
[gunshots and thumps]

75
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,578
[thumps and gunshots]

76
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,580
[snipping]

77
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,709
[electronic blipping]

78
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:54,007
[music fades]

79
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:56,634
[phone rings]

80
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,969
Oh, no!

81
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:04,225
Mr. Regalia.

82
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:07,228
Mercado, by any chance,

83
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:09,230
did you speak with my daughter?

84
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:10,315
Audrey.

85
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:11,149
[tense music playing]

86
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,108
She contacted me.

87
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:14,360
She's asking help from my tracker.

88
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:18,656
Didn't I ask you not to deal
with my daughter?

89
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,783
[in English] And now, you're doing
the exact opposite

90
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:22,577
of what I told you to do!

91
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:24,662
Your daughter also asked us

92
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:27,248
not to tell you that we spoke,

93
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:30,668
which is also her right as a client.

94
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:35,548
Now, uh, well, I'm not taking sides.

95
00:03:36,174 --> 00:03:38,301
[in English] The Master Cutter is hired

96
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:41,596
for his expertise, not his loyalty.

97
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:43,890
[in English] Okay.

98
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:48,228
Again, I'm asking you.

99
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:49,854
[tense music playing]

100
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:51,898
[in English] Tell your tracker
to back off.

101
00:03:51,981 --> 00:03:54,817
[Dmitri] <i>And don't meet with my daughter.</i>

102
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:56,903
I'll pay you.

103
00:03:56,986 --> 00:03:59,197
I'll double the price.

104
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:02,325
No charge for the trouble.

105
00:04:02,408 --> 00:04:04,661
We're easy to deal with.

106
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:08,414
[in English] Also,
and I say this respectfully,

107
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:14,629
this is the last time that I will
transact with any of you Regalias.

108
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:18,967
Family drama is bad luck for business.

109
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:21,302
[in English] Okay.

110
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:23,638
[in English] I will update you.

111
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:36,818
[suspicious music playing]

112
00:04:54,377 --> 00:04:55,336
Netchai…

113
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,715
Forgive me, okay?

114
00:05:00,216 --> 00:05:01,968
It's my fault why…

115
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:05,888
why you ended up
in that situation, because…

116
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:09,475
I let you get close to that man.

117
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:14,230
Don't blame yourself, Big Brother.

118
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,356
Hmm.

119
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:17,317
[sniffles]

120
00:05:18,484 --> 00:05:20,111
That was my fault.

121
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:22,739
It was my fault because I'm your brother.

122
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:26,075
I should be the one protecting… [winces]

123
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:30,413
I should be the one protecting you, right?

124
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:34,375
But look, the opposite happened.

125
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:38,254
Because what? Because I let my pride
get the better of me.

126
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:44,969
You know, honestly, I really didn't…

127
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,180
I really didn't do anything there.

128
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:48,139
‪[melancholic music playing]

129
00:05:48,222 --> 00:05:49,599
It was Atoy.

130
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:52,185
[sniffles] Atoy.

131
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:53,686
It was all Atoy.

132
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:58,191
Atoy did all of that.
He's the tough one, and he's good.

133
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:00,068
Ha, look…

134
00:06:00,151 --> 00:06:01,152
[titters]

135
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:03,362
You were the one who got kidnapped.

136
00:06:03,446 --> 00:06:05,573
And I was the one who ended up
in the hospital, look.

137
00:06:05,656 --> 00:06:07,492
[moans, sniffles]

138
00:06:07,575 --> 00:06:11,454
I don't need someone tough and good.

139
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:15,708
You, going with him
to save me, Big Brother,

140
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:19,295
means you still cared about me.

141
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:22,006
[stammers] And it's not just caring.

142
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,133
‪[sentimental music playing]

143
00:06:24,258 --> 00:06:27,595
Of course, I also regret that, because…

144
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:29,472
I forgot you for years.

145
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:32,225
[Tonet inhales, exhales, sniffles]

146
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,684
That's over.

147
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:37,563
That's over, okay? [sniffles and chuckles]

148
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:40,858
And don't call me "Netchai" anymore.

149
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:43,611
- Sounds like a provincial baby name.
- [Emerson chuckles]

150
00:06:43,694 --> 00:06:44,821
I'm so pretty now,

151
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:46,948
and you still call me that.

152
00:06:47,031 --> 00:06:48,032
Just call me Tonet.

153
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:50,785
Okay, okay, okay, okay. Me too, me too.

154
00:06:50,868 --> 00:06:52,703
Don't call me Manong anymore, okay?

155
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:55,331
You called me Manong in front of them.
It makes me sound old.

156
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:56,457
Just call me Brother.

157
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,126
Or Grandpa. That's better--

158
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,710
- No! Just Brother.
- Okay.

159
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:03,589
All right, Brother Emerson.

160
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,634
[in Visayan] I will make it up to you.

161
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:10,638
[in Visayan] You don't have to. I am okay.

162
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:11,848
[chuckles]

163
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:14,642
[sentimental music intensifies]

164
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:23,359
[chuckles]

165
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:24,402
There. [sniffles]

166
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,237
We're close now.

167
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,823
They won't tease us anymore.

168
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:30,366
[chuckles]

169
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,743
Do you feel pain anywhere?

170
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,995
[guttural inhale]

171
00:07:34,078 --> 00:07:35,413
No more. [inhales]

172
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:38,583
- [mysterious music playing]
- [door clicks shut]

173
00:07:40,376 --> 00:07:41,669
My shades.

174
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:43,463
Where are they?

175
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:46,466
[Mercado] <i>Garden area, 10:30 a.m.</i>
<i>Don't be late.</i>

176
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:50,052
It's 10:27 already. [sharp inhale]

177
00:07:57,685 --> 00:08:01,606
- [suspicious music playing]
- [phone ringing]

178
00:08:03,941 --> 00:08:05,026
[in English] Yes, sir?

179
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,236
[Mercado, in English]
<i>Abort engagement with Audrey Regalia.</i>

180
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:11,574
Mr. Regalia asked not to meet
with his daughter.

181
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:14,452
[in English] All right.
Uh, copy that, sir.

182
00:08:14,535 --> 00:08:17,872
Um, I haven't established
contact with the subject yet.

183
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:24,170
[tense music playing]

184
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:26,631
Miss?

185
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:29,800
Miss in yellow, is this yours?

186
00:08:31,385 --> 00:08:32,678
Um, miss?

187
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:34,764
- Is this yours?
- Uh, no.

188
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:39,810
[pensive music playing]

189
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,573
[clicks tongue, sighs]

190
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:54,116
[softly] Where could I have left it?

191
00:08:56,118 --> 00:08:57,370
[gasps] Excuse me.

192
00:08:57,453 --> 00:08:59,705
[both stuttering]

193
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:01,374
Okay, I won't move anymore.

194
00:09:01,457 --> 00:09:03,584
- Stay here.
- [in English] Uh, thanks.

195
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,838
Uh, do you know if there's
a lost and found here?

196
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:09,131
[in English] Lost and found?

197
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,675
Just ask at the reception.

198
00:09:10,758 --> 00:09:12,552
There are many of them there.
I really need to pee.

199
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:13,636
- Ah.
- Yes

200
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:15,346
- Okay, thanks.
- Okay, bye.

201
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:21,644
- Miss.
- [in English] Yes, sir?

202
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:26,148
You weren't here earlier, right?

203
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,025
- Yes. My colleague was on duty earlier.
- [stammers]

204
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,945
I took something
from your colleague, because…

205
00:09:31,028 --> 00:09:31,946
Um, I helped her.

206
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:34,365
I was supposed to hand this
to the one who left it.

207
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:37,994
But I didn't see the owner anymore, so…

208
00:09:38,077 --> 00:09:38,911
I'll just return it here.

209
00:09:38,995 --> 00:09:40,830
Maybe they'll come back here
to retrieve it.

210
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:42,206
Ah, okay, sir.

211
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,291
- All right.
- Thank you.

212
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:46,210
[phone rings]

213
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:49,505
[Atoy] Hello?

214
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:50,673
No, I'm still here.

215
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:53,301
Let's just meet at the canteen.

216
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,220
Okay.

217
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:07,023
Miss. Uh, is there a lost and found here?

218
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,441
Because my shades are missing.

219
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:10,568
They're my favorite.

220
00:10:10,651 --> 00:10:11,902
Uh, is this it, ma'am?

221
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:14,322
Because a man left this here.

222
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,406
[in English] Oh, thank God.

223
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,658
Uh, where is the man?

224
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:18,993
He already left.

225
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:22,163
- Too bad.
- Uh, what's your name, ma'am?

226
00:10:22,246 --> 00:10:24,707
So, you can receive your shades.

227
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:27,793
- Just sign here.
- Okay. Audrey Regalia.

228
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,754
[suspicious music playing]

229
00:10:29,837 --> 00:10:31,797
- Okay. Thank you.
- Thank you.

230
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:33,090
Bye.

231
00:10:36,844 --> 00:10:39,889
So, this Master Cutter
is a tracker of people?

232
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:41,057
Not a tailor?

233
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:45,561
[in English] Yes,
and that's his code name.

234
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:46,729
[in English] Don't ask me why.

235
00:10:48,397 --> 00:10:50,358
He doesn't just find people.

236
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,445
The Kelso I asked you to find

237
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:58,074
for months, which you couldn't…

238
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,451
[in English] He did it in one week.

239
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:02,662
[smirks, then sniffs]

240
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:04,080
Well, he's the expert then.

241
00:11:05,414 --> 00:11:07,333
And now Audrey wants to hire him

242
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:10,670
to look for this guy
she met on the island.

243
00:11:11,545 --> 00:11:12,963
He'll definitely find him,

244
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:16,550
if the transaction pushes through.

245
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,303
[in English] So, he's like a human GPS,

246
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:21,972
spy, greyhound rolled into one.

247
00:11:23,307 --> 00:11:26,560
Then he must be paid a lot.

248
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,562
Is that all you can say?

249
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:33,526
Of course, because nothing's at stake
for you if he finds that man!

250
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:35,319
[in English] I'm sorry, Dad.

251
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:37,196
- I just thought--
- Shh!

252
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:39,073
[sinister music playing]

253
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:43,452
That guy can open
a can of worms, or worse…

254
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:47,373
pick old wounds that have long healed.

255
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:01,512
[pensive music playing]

256
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,351
[phone clicks]

257
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,442
[line ringing]

258
00:12:14,525 --> 00:12:15,526
Hello, Tonet.

259
00:12:16,152 --> 00:12:17,570
This café is closed.

260
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,530
Let's just meet at the garden.

261
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:23,117
Okay.

262
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:35,463
[Audrey] Could this be him?

263
00:12:37,298 --> 00:12:39,758
He didn't even say
if it's hot or iced coffee.

264
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:45,473
[mysterious music playing]

265
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:46,557
[clears throat]

266
00:12:47,683 --> 00:12:49,185
Master Cutter?

267
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,567
M-Master?

268
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,114
Cutter?

269
00:13:04,074 --> 00:13:05,075
Hi!

270
00:13:06,035 --> 00:13:07,953
You're so young.

271
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:09,955
Ma'am?

272
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:12,791
I don't know you.

273
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:18,672
[girl] Hey, Paul! Let's go!

274
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:22,426
[music swells]

275
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:23,928
[girl] Who's that auntie
you're talking to?

276
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,137
[Paul] I don't even know her.

277
00:13:25,221 --> 00:13:27,348
- "Auntie", really?!
- [Paul] She just talked to me.

278
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:29,517
Unbelievable.

279
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:34,855
[Audrey] Where is he?

280
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:36,482
[line ringing]

281
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:39,652
[Audrey, in English] Come on, pick up.

282
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:46,534
[gentle music playing]

283
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,425
Why is she here again?

284
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:12,309
[in English] Uh, excuse me!

285
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:13,727
[in English] Those are my shades.

286
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,855
[music intensifies]

287
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:24,488
- [sentimental music playing]
- [dramatic stinging]

288
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:37,710
[gasps of relief]

289
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:39,837
- How are you?
- [in English] How are you?

290
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,422
I'm okay.

291
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:42,756
I- I'm okay.

292
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,467
- Um, still alive.
- Yes, I'm fine.

293
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:46,719
Wow! [chuckles]

294
00:14:48,053 --> 00:14:49,221
[chuckles softly]

295
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:51,223
You look so different.

296
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:52,892
- You do too.
- [Atoy chuckles]

297
00:14:53,475 --> 00:14:54,643
Wow!

298
00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:56,478
[gentle music playing]

299
00:14:56,562 --> 00:14:57,855
It's been so long
since we last saw each other.

300
00:14:57,938 --> 00:15:00,232
- [in English] It's been eight years.
- [in English] E-eight… Eight years, right?

301
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:02,318
- Yeah.
- Wow, unbelievable!

302
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:05,487
So, what are you doing here? Um…

303
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:08,365
Are you visiting someone,

304
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,702
a patient, or family--
What about you? Are you okay?

305
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:14,288
Uh, I'm fine. Um, no, I'm…

306
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:17,249
I'm just meeting…

307
00:15:19,209 --> 00:15:21,420
someone. [titters]

308
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:23,422
Here? Here, in…

309
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,507
the garden?

310
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:27,885
[mysterious music playing]

311
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:31,597
Here, in the garden.

312
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:39,772
[Atoy scoffs]

313
00:15:40,606 --> 00:15:44,193
[suspenseful music playing]

314
00:15:44,276 --> 00:15:45,444
You're Audrey?

315
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:49,823
Audrey Regalia?

316
00:15:51,492 --> 00:15:53,369
[dramatic whoosh]

317
00:15:57,081 --> 00:15:58,707
How did you know?

318
00:15:58,791 --> 00:15:59,917
[titters]

319
00:16:00,834 --> 00:16:03,545
Why… Why did you introduce
yourself to me as Elaine?

320
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:08,050
- That's so different. Audrey, Elaine3
- [scoffs] Wait a minute.

321
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:13,013
As for you, I still don't know
your real name until now.

322
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,473
Oh? Ah, wait.

323
00:16:14,556 --> 00:16:17,017
I told you why, didn't I?

324
00:16:17,101 --> 00:16:18,978
- I told you why!
- Why? Why?

325
00:16:19,603 --> 00:16:23,315
I had a mission back on the island.
I was looking for someone.

326
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,275
Didn't we talk about this before?

327
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:26,360
[in English] Mission.

328
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:31,490
So that's why you used the people there…

329
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:34,618
including me…

330
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:37,246
[music swells]

331
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,289
- …to blend in.
- Wait, wait.

332
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:42,501
I didn't use anyone, especially not you.

333
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:44,586
It just so happened
that's the nature of my work.

334
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,629
Wow!

335
00:16:45,713 --> 00:16:46,672
- Wow, huh!
- Elaine… Oh, Elaine,

336
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:47,631
Audrey, c'mon.

337
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:50,300
So, what? You were going
to dump me anyway, right?

338
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:52,511
We had an agreement back then.

339
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,513
Didn't we have an agreement?

340
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:56,473
That we'd meet at your house.

341
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:58,600
I went to your house.

342
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:01,270
I came back, but you didn't show up.

343
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,732
And this necklace of mine.

344
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:06,775
Do you remember this?
It's important to me. It's…

345
00:17:06,859 --> 00:17:09,194
You just threw it in the trash. Oh?

346
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,613
Why are you acting like that?

347
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:15,617
[sighs]

348
00:17:18,620 --> 00:17:20,622
You're too full of yourself, you know?

349
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,167
What do you think of me, huh?

350
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,627
That I couldn't move on from you?

351
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:27,838
That I don't have a life?

352
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:30,966
[scoffs] For your information…

353
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:36,555
eight years passed,
and you never crossed my mind.

354
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:37,931
[tense music playing]

355
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:38,932
[in English] Never?

356
00:17:41,602 --> 00:17:44,980
You don't want her to find
what she's looking for.

357
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,149
[in English] I'm just looking out for her.

358
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,609
[in English] It's for her own good.

359
00:17:48,692 --> 00:17:52,362
What, sir? Maybe…
she wants to find her ex-boyfriend, right?

360
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:55,157
Or maybe a man who cheated on her.

361
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,910
[music swells]

362
00:17:57,993 --> 00:17:58,869
Really?

363
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:05,000
Well…

364
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:07,795
Eight years.

365
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:11,548
With all the boyfriends
you must have had after me,

366
00:18:11,632 --> 00:18:13,592
- then surely--
- [in English] Excuse me?!

367
00:18:13,675 --> 00:18:15,469
You were never my boyfriend!

368
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:20,766
You're just some random guy I met
on the island who's easy to forget!

369
00:18:21,266 --> 00:18:24,561
[dramatic music playing]

370
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:25,604
Oh, really?

371
00:18:26,396 --> 00:18:28,482
[music swells]

372
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:35,614
[phone ringing]

373
00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:37,449
Mr. Mercado.

374
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:40,202
Mr. Regalia, confirming no contact

375
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:43,539
between The Master Cutter
and Audrey Regalia.

376
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:45,707
Thank you very much.

377
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:49,294
Sorry again for the trouble
caused by my daughter and me.

378
00:18:49,378 --> 00:18:52,548
[tense music playing]

379
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:56,885
[chuckles]

380
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:02,432
You know, Dad, Audrey can always
find other ways, right?

381
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:04,935
[in English] She'll eventually
give up. [sighs]

382
00:19:06,019 --> 00:19:07,396
[in English] That Master Cutter…

383
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,899
is her last resort.

384
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:11,984
[smirks]

385
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:16,321
[tense music playing]

386
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:18,907
[phone rings]

387
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:21,702
[in English] Hello, Dad?

388
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,079
Oh, Audrey.

389
00:19:24,663 --> 00:19:25,581
Where are you?

390
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:26,540
[pensive music playing]

391
00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:27,499
[Audrey, in English] I'm just in Makati.

392
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,793
Um, having brunch with a friend.
Do you need something?

393
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:33,839
[sighs] I was hoping you could
come with me to your mom's grave.

394
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:35,507
It's our anniversary today.

395
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:38,844
Sorry. Um, I'll try to follow, Dad.

396
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:41,513
Atoy.

397
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:52,191
Dad…

398
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:55,819
[gentle music playing]

399
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:58,822
[in English] I wish I can find a love
like yours and Mom's.

400
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:01,450
You were always there for each other,

401
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:03,327
even if you didn't see
each other for a long time.

402
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,828
[in English] I'm sure you will.

403
00:20:07,956 --> 00:20:08,916
Bye.

404
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:21,220
Atoy, sorry, it took me
a while to get here.

405
00:20:21,303 --> 00:20:22,971
Turns out there are two gardens here.

406
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:25,182
I went to the one in the other wing.

407
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:27,601
Uh, what was it…
What were you going to say?

408
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:31,605
I just wanted to thank you in person.

409
00:20:31,688 --> 00:20:35,025
Thank you for saving
my and my brother's life.

410
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:37,694
- [sentimental music playing]
- [scoffs]

411
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:40,197
It's nothing.

412
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,241
Anyone would have done it.

413
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:44,534
And you didn't hesitate

414
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:49,790
to save him, even though I know
your history together was not ideal.

415
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:53,085
I just want to thank you
because you lengthened

416
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:54,795
our time as siblings.

417
00:20:55,504 --> 00:21:00,259
If not for you,
and had he been fatally hurt,

418
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:03,929
maybe he'd only remember me
as a bad sister.

419
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:06,056
What are you saying? Don't say that.

420
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:08,892
He was worried about you
when you went missing.

421
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:11,812
You know, the depth
of his resentment toward you,

422
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:14,815
it comes from his love for you.

423
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:17,985
Sometimes those things
just get obscured, okay?

424
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:20,445
It's just a matter of talking.

425
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:22,781
- [in English] Thank you, Atoy.
- Of course.

426
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:27,119
Mmm, alright then.

427
00:21:27,828 --> 00:21:28,662
Hmm.

428
00:21:30,372 --> 00:21:31,415
There.

429
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:35,669
[melancholic music playing]

430
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:06,992
[seat belt lock clicks]

431
00:22:08,952 --> 00:22:12,706
With all the boyfriends
you must have had after me, then surely…

432
00:22:12,789 --> 00:22:13,832
[in English] Excuse me?!

433
00:22:13,915 --> 00:22:15,834
You were never my boyfriend!

434
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:20,881
You're just some random guy I met
on the island who's easy to forget!

435
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:22,382
Really?

436
00:22:23,216 --> 00:22:25,844
[melancholic music playing]

437
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:30,724
He just used you, Audrey.

438
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:33,894
[music swells]

439
00:22:35,479 --> 00:22:40,567
[wailing]

440
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:57,000
[sobs]

441
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:02,339
[wailing]

442
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:05,467
[sentimental music playing]

443
00:23:39,626 --> 00:23:41,253
[in English] Oh, hello!

444
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:46,925
[in English] My beautiful,
evil sister-in-law!

445
00:23:47,008 --> 00:23:48,802
[tense music playing]

446
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,470
[in English] You're so pretty today.

447
00:23:50,554 --> 00:23:54,099
[in English] Wow. Somebody's
a little drunk and happy tonight?

448
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:55,392
Where did you come from?

449
00:23:57,769 --> 00:23:59,729
Do you think we don't know
what you're doing?

450
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:01,690
You're still looking for your man.

451
00:24:01,773 --> 00:24:03,066
And now you're drinking.

452
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,609
What are you doing, Audrey, huh?

453
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,361
Who are you, huh?!

454
00:24:06,444 --> 00:24:07,529
Are you my mother?!

455
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,865
- [Dmitri] Red!
- Mind your actions.

456
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,074
- [Dmitri] Let her go!
- I--

457
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,206
Audrey.

458
00:24:19,166 --> 00:24:22,586
[in English] Audrey, there's no point
in looking for that man.

459
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:27,007
So that's why you stopped me from talking
to the tracker behind my back?

460
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:29,467
[tense music playing]

461
00:24:30,177 --> 00:24:31,386
[in English] Don't worry, Dad.

462
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:34,264
I'm not mad at you, because…

463
00:24:36,099 --> 00:24:37,309
you're right.

464
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:41,188
He means nothing in my life.

465
00:24:42,522 --> 00:24:45,025
[in English] We mean nothing
to each other.

466
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:47,694
I want to leave this place.

467
00:24:47,777 --> 00:24:50,405
[in English] I just want to get back
to my life in the States.

468
00:24:51,364 --> 00:24:54,451
[in English] Finally, you've come
to your senses.

469
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,078
[in English] But promise me
one thing, Dad.

470
00:24:58,747 --> 00:25:00,498
[in English] Don't ever do that again.

471
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:04,127
I didn't like what you did,

472
00:25:04,211 --> 00:25:06,504
blocking my plan to meet that man.

473
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:09,549
[in English] I trust you so much.

474
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:13,637
I don't want you hiding things from me.

475
00:25:15,138 --> 00:25:16,640
And most of all…

476
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:20,185
I don't want lies.

477
00:25:21,561 --> 00:25:23,104
[music swells]

478
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:29,861
[suspicious music playing]

479
00:25:54,844 --> 00:26:00,600
- [electronic blipping]
- [tense music playing]

480
00:26:04,854 --> 00:26:07,524
- [Gavin, in English] <i>Are you okay?</i>
- [Audrey] <i>My side just hurts.</i>

481
00:26:07,607 --> 00:26:09,025
[in English] It's been happening
a lot lately.

482
00:26:09,109 --> 00:26:10,568
Have you had it checked, Auntie?

483
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:13,029
Different matter, different woman.

484
00:26:13,113 --> 00:26:15,699
That's just expenses
and headaches. Not worth it.

485
00:26:15,782 --> 00:26:18,118
I wasn't talking about a girlfriend!

486
00:26:18,201 --> 00:26:20,328
Am I going to school?

487
00:26:20,412 --> 00:26:21,663
[in English] Surprise!

488
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:24,582
[in English] Welcome
to your student girl era!

489
00:26:24,666 --> 00:26:25,834
I don't want to go to school.

490
00:26:25,917 --> 00:26:26,835
- [Ame] Huh?
- [Ibyang] Hey, wait.

491
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:28,169
Okay, it's up to you then.

492
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:29,129
- [Ame] Ibyang!
- Psst, hey--

493
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:31,214
[Audrey] The doctor here said

494
00:26:32,090 --> 00:26:37,304
this scar is from a cesarean section
and not an appendectomy.

495
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:39,556
Was I pregnant then?

496
00:26:39,639 --> 00:26:42,017
We'll have no control
when your father gets involved.

497
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:45,103
He'll get angrier and find a way
to look for the child!

498
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:47,314
And then he once mentioned that he knew…

499
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:48,815
The Master Cutter.

500
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:49,649
‪UP NEXT

501
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:50,650
He can't get ahead of us.

502
00:26:51,234 --> 00:26:52,902
[Atoy] Norma Cruz.

503
00:26:53,486 --> 00:26:54,571
She's the one who found him?

504
00:26:54,654 --> 00:26:55,739
She's a nun.

505
00:26:55,822 --> 00:26:57,741
Do you know what congregation
she belongs to?

506
00:26:57,824 --> 00:27:00,160
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

507
00:27:00,243 --> 00:27:03,038
♪ <i>One cut, and the matter is over</i> ♪
